            <entry xml:id="entry_ar" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                <form xml:id="form_d3485e66" type="lemma"><orth>ar</orth><form xml:id="form_d3485e68" type="variant"><orth>aræ</orth></form></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3485e74"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>оглобля</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>thill, shaft</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d3485e84">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3485e86">
                        <quote>sæ kinʒʒon wærdun ævzestæ aræ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у них колесница невесты c серебряными оглоблями</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they have the bride's chariot with silver shafts</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>62%l346%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3485e105">
                        <quote>Toturi kond je ʽfsoj, Toturi kond æ ar</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в день (божества) Тотур сделано ее (сохи) ярмо, в день Тотур сделано
                                дышло</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>on the day of the deity Totur, its (of the plough) yoke was made, on
                                the day of Totur, its drawbar was made</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            143</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/> ‘рука’. Для отпадения
                    конечного <hi rendition="#rend_italic">m</hi> в дигорском ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ǧar"/> (из
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ǧarm</hi>) ‘теплый’, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">car</hi> (из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_carm"/>) ‘шкура’ и
                    др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>379</biblScope></bibl>). Значение ‘оглобля’ для <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar(m)</hi>,
                    наряду с основным значением ‘рука’, подтверждается также терминами <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardwan"/> (из <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar-dawæn</hi>) ‘рашпиль’, буквально
                    „то, чем шлифуют оглоблю“, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærmbos"/> ‘гужовка’,
                    буквально „перевязь оглобли“, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_artʼæng"/> „ременная
                    веревка у саней“. Перенос анатомических названий на орудия производства,
                    средства передвижения и пр. обычен: ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e209" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e144" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>ручка</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e223" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e149" xml:lang="ru"><w>ножка</w></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e236" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e152" xml:lang="ru"><w>крыло</w></mentioned> и т. п. В частности, для
                    семантики ‘рука’ → ‘оглобля’ ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e242" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e155" xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>armaī</w>
                        <gloss><q>оглобля</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e250" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e164" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>xelna</w>
                        <gloss><q>оглобля</q></gloss></mentioned> от <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e258" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e172" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>xeli</w>
                        <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>. Основные названия средств
                    передвижения и упряжи относятся в осетинском к иранскому фонду, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsonʒ"/>. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>54, 119,
                            362</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/> ‘hand’. As for the
                    drop of the final <hi rendition="#rend_italic">m</hi> in Digor, cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ǧar"/> (from
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ǧarm</hi>) ‘warm’, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">car</hi> (from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_carm"/>) ‘skin’
                    etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>379</biblScope></bibl>). The meaning ‘shaft’ for <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar(m)</hi>, in
                    addition to the main meaning ‘hand’, is proven by such terms as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardwan"/> (from <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar-dawæn</hi>) ‘rasp’, literally ‘thing that
                    is used to grind the shaft’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærmbos"/> ‘cartage’,
                    literally ‘shaft sling’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_artʼæng"/> ‘sled rope’.
                    The transfer of anatomical names to tools of production, vehicles, etc. is
                    common: cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e144" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e209" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>ručka</w>
                        <gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3485e217" xml:lang="ru"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>handle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e149" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e223" xml:lang="ru"><w>nožka</w>
                        <gloss><q>leg</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3485e229" xml:lang="ru"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>stem</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e152" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e236" xml:lang="ru"><w>krylo</w>
                        <gloss><q>wing</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. In particular, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e155" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e242" xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>armaī</w>
                        <gloss><q>thill, shaft</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e164" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e250" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>xelna</w>
                        <gloss><q>thill</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3485e172" xml:id="mentioned_d3485e258" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>xeli</w>
                        <gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned> for the semantics of ‘hand’ →
                    ‘shaft’. The main names of vehicles and harnesses refer to the Iranian fund in
                    Ossetic, see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsonʒ"/>. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arm"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>54, 119, 362</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
